at his disposal.} Bb7 ({Natural development - a relatively unexplored 
alternative is} 11... b4 {.}) 12. Bd3 {[%cal Bh2h4] White completes development 
and intends to build up his kingside attack with h4.} e5 $1 {[%cal Gd3e4][%csl 
Rd3,Re4] I've chosen this variation to showcase this other idea, which is 
typical of this variation. The bishop on d3 is made to look stupid with the 
blocked central pawns.} 13. Be3 Bb4 $11 {[%cal Gb4c3,Gc7c3,Be8g8,Ba8c8][%csl 
Rc3] Black has fully equalised.} *

