1. e4 c5 ({White has a number of Anti-Sicilians at his disposal. To provide you 
with a more comprehensive repertoire, we have covered some of White's most 
common choices, however some of white's slightly more offbeat options - such as} 
c5 2. Na3 {- have been ommitted since they are rarely seen.}) 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 
{[%cal Gd2d4,Bf1g2] White wants to keep the option of d4 in one go open, but 
there is a trade-off...} d5 $1 {[%csl Re4] Unlike 3. d3, 3. g3 isn't perfectly 
prepared to meet this move.} 4. exd5 exd5 5. d4 Nf6 {[%cal Bf8e7,Be8g8] Black 
intends to castle as quickly as possible.} 6. Bg2 Be7 7. O-O O-O 8. dxc5 Bxc5 
$11 {[%cal Bb8c6,Bc8g4,Bf8e8,Ba7a6] Black has a decent IQP position since his 
pieces all have good squares available.} *

